caption: The bourbon cider and spiked cocoa are delicious. Great little gem to find right now.

Love this place. During the summer/early fall when dine-in was an option, we were here almost weekly. Burgers are awesome, so are the salads. Plus, Ryan and staff are awesome. Will do our best to support them to keep them up and running.

What a great spot! They've got cute string lights up everywhere and the whole place has a good vibe. I think they're even doing to-go cocktails from the look of the little set up they have out front. They also have spiked chai and bourbon cider which were great! The food was so/so but wouldn't deter me from visiting again to be sure! Highly recommend!

Came in for carry out. So happy we did! Burger was perfect! Grilled Cheese was amazing! They were selling margaritas to go!! Owners are SUPER nice! They were even selling baking supplies ad cookie kits!!! We'll be back!!

Racine Burger was 10/10. Would definitely recommend if you're a burger fanatic. Ryan was awesome both on the phone and in person, during these times it was a breath of fresh air to have someone as welcoming and friendly as he was. 100% will be back next chance I get.
Good menu.  Good  whisk/ scotch.  Bartender make good drinks
Friendly and the burger was very good.
Warm, welcoming neighborhood bar with great service and a solid cocktail and beer menu.
great neighborhood bar with nice service and good food

You might go by this place a hundred times and not know it's a great bar.  They have a nice beer list that covers all the bases and the food is very good too.  I had the Pastrami snadwich with fries and it was delicious - thank god I only ordered the half sandwich cuz it was huge.  The back room is another surprise too - a full bar with a large skylight that makes the small area seem spacious.   Service was also great.  It's just a solid neighborhood bar.

Moved in across the street and this was the first place in the neighborhood that I tried. It’s amazing. Service was great. Atmosphere was great. Bathrooms were spotless. Burgers were awesome. The menu is very limited, but it’s better to only have a few things and do them really well than have a bunch of stuff you don’t know how to do right.

Great food, good vibes for watching games and an excellent burger menu with crazy customizations. Pictured below is a chorizo, jalapeño cheese burger. Mixed with the atmosphere of sporting games makes an excellent place.
Nice drinks, the place looks fancy.
New vibe is solid.  Decent food options as well.  A good local haunt.
Treated me very nice soon as I came in, I recommend this place has good food and chill area!!!
Worst chicken and waffles I had ever had. The waffles were sour! But chicken quesadilla was good.

I came here to watch the Cowboys game not realizing it was a Giant's bar. They were playing each other that night. Despite the potential awkwardness, I found the crowd relatively welcoming and made a couple friends. They had a good selection of drafts and a killer Wing deal. Also feels pretty good to be the one guy in the room cheering when everyone else is shaking their fist.
Saturday night, college football, crazy busy. Service was good, food was great. Folks around us laughing, having fun. So glad we ate here
Most fun bar I’ve been to in Chicago
Nice neighborhood bar with delicious food and something for everyone
Awesome! Giants rule bar!
Wings burgers and cheap beer. Sports on tv. Be ready. That is the vibe here. For sports bar lovers, heaven.

Such a great atmosphere and really great food. I have to say though; don't get the bloody mary. It is very bland. I love this place so much though that I can't take away a star just for one item. If you're not sure what to get, the nachos are the bomb. I crave them way too often. It's one of our go to weeknight spots and one you should seriously consider trying out.
Solid brunch spot with an all you can drink special, seems to be a popular spot for F1 races, so show up early if it is race day!
Fine bar. Great selection. Tried their Ghost Pepper wings. Boy, were they a challenge! I got through 4 of them while I dressed the other 4 with a Carolina Reaper sauce I brought in myself.
Great food great for watching sports all kinds of beers decent prices

Overall: A solid sports bar option to watch any type of game, with good food and cheap beer to go with it.  The good: On an NFL playoff night it was very busy, but our server was always accommodating and cheery. The specials were great that night ($5 wings and $12 pitchers) and the food was all tasty, with the boneless wings being a standout. The buffalo sauce had a great kick that wasn't too generic but also not overwhelming. The atmosphere is clean and doesn't try too hard to be anything, which works. They have plenty of TVs to go around.  The not-so-good: Some of the food was "meh". The mac and cheese was disappointing, and the brussel sprouts were good but not nearly large enough in portion size.  Atmosphere: 8/10 Service: 9/10 Food: 8/10
Everything is reasonably priced and the burgers are AMAZING.  Great place to go and watch a game, especially NY teams!
Great place for trivia
Sick menu, bro.
I've given them a lot of my monies.
Great giants bar - good service, good drinks, good cheese fries
LGR! Came in for an afternoon Rangers game and because Notre Dame was also playing, Guinness was only $5 a pint. Great meal too.
The place kicked the utmost ass. The food was excellent and the service was on POINT. The bartenders hold it down and will make your night. As a Chicago native, Be there soon.

We had a wonderful experience here. We were trying to watch the Bills game, and they were kind enough to search for it, and turn it on in a room full of folks who weren't interested. We had a few drinks, and our party ordered a taco (which was good), and a few bowls of elote. I highly recommend the elote! Great atmosphere, too!
Really spacious and comfortable interior with plenty of options for watching any sports you could possibly think of. The staff was also extremely friendly and took very personal care of us!

In spite of being a Notre Dame and NY Giants bar on a day full of college football games, they happily put a Premier League game on for us. Staff engaged in really friendly conversation with us the entire time and made our trip a lot more memorable.
Exceptional service. Friendly staff. Good food and clean, and friendly patrons.
Great food, service and easy going patrons. Chill here and watch your favorite sports.
Service was pretty quick, food was tasty, and the pork belly tacos were on point
Pretty cool looking bar with a great open window seating area in front. Staff is really great and sliders are awesome. They have a half off slider special for happy hour.
Fun atmosphere. Live sports and many drink options. Not too loud either.
Had a birthday party with a large group of friends. We were provided with a reserved space and everyone had great fun. The ambience and feel of this place is amazing. Would come back again!!
Great Giants bar! Good beer good prices nice atmosphere
Awesome spot. Great food, nice beer, and all for a relatively low price. Definitely be coming back
We were here for a party and the staff was very accommodating. They were quick with the wrist bands and very very helpful

I'm a NY Rangers fan and went to Racine during the one of the NYR Stanley Cup Playoff games while visiting Chicago for work. It was a little bit of a pain to get to, but I had a great time once we were there. The servers were really nice, and the beer and food were really good. Also, all the TVs had the game on and everyone was a fan, so that made the experience extra nice. I didn't find anything wrong with the food at all, but it also wasn't anything worth writing home about either. Also, it took a long time to prepare. Our server said they had a new chef, which was causing the hold up.  I definitely recommend Racine, especially if you want to watch any New York sporting events.
Great food, awesome staff, clean and well lit, especially towards the back. Will definitely be back there.

Went for Trvia night. We decided to order food and I got one of the many burgers available. Not sure if I overlooked it but it didn't come with fries. It was half price whiskey night and I was downing crown royal for $4, not a bad deal in the city. I would definitely go back
Sponsored my football team, great owners and good food. Nice wintertime spot to eat and drink.
Awesome bar, great staff and great drinks!

I usually go here for NY Rangers games, but it's a great bar/restaurant for anyone. Food is great (try the nachos if you're sharing), there are good specials every day (1/2 price whiskey on Wednesday!), and the beer/liquor selection is solid. For those wanting to catch some out-of-town games, this is a NY Giants, NY Rangers, and Notre Dame bar, and they'll usually show other NY games (Mets/Jets/etc.) when there's demand. The staff is always nice and attentive, and I have a great time whenever I go.

Daily specials for good pub food and a decent selection of craft beers on tap along with a full bar. Known as a NY bar, Rangers and Giants games are played on the many TVs. The bar has two sections that often play different games, if you prefer one over another when both are playing. They also offer trivia in that back area on Wednesdays.

Good neighborhood bar, take it or leave it type of place for me though. Beers taste flat and like the taps need to be cleaned out, basic cocktails you can order from any bar. Full menu which is nice but it's mostly heavy bar food.
The most racist venue I have been in since I moved to Chicago. The bodyguard outside put his hands on me and I plan on filing legal action
Good feel to the place.
Great food, great drinks, great people.  I went there as a Rangers fan but would gladly go any time!!!
crazy! go rangers

Racine Plumbing has sponsored my rec league softball team for the past few years.  The staff and management have been a delight to work with.  They only have 8 beers on tap, but of the 8, there is always something that you typically cannot get at other places. The food is top-notch all around, but I would especially recommend the brunch menu.  While it can get somewhat loud at night, the brunch or early dinner atmosphere is a little more toned down, and makes it a great place to get a meal and have a good conversation.
This place is underrated, I think mostly because its not on a main bar strip. It is never too crowded, but always delivers. I hope that more people find out about Racine Plumbing!

Went to trivia here one night with some friends. Food was solid. trivia was fun. Got really loud and crowded though and the service was a little slow because of it. Would come back but wasn't the biggest fan of the format of trivia. Lots of tv's though so great for watching a game or something
Pretty good burgers.  My wife says that they are the best.

I've spent the last two weekends here, really great spot. They've got good drink specials & my friends and I found the food really good. What other bar/pub do you know of that serves Chicken & Waffles?
Amazing food for a bar plus a great Sunday brunch special. The staff is friendly and the atmosphere works.
